title: Grateful Dead Live at Cameron Indoor Stadium, Duke U on 1982-04-02
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues-> Sugaree, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loser, Little Red Rooster, Candyman, Looks Like Rain-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, It Must Have Been The Roses, Women Are Smarter, He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

Jerry and Phil swap sides

reviews.review_text:
Error explained I just discovered I made a HUGE mistake with these tapes.

This is NOT from my masters.
It is another copy I was given by my old friend Laser Beam.
(I grabbed the wrong tapes out of the storage box.)

The taper HERE is unknown & I SURE hope it isn't from a source that has circulated.
I certainly cannot claim that I recorded it because I didn't. This was just my mistake or "human error" if you will.

I grabbed the wrong tapes & just NOW discovered my error.

My masters don't sound HALF this good & that's why I had never traded them.
(Once I had THESE tapes, I knew there was WAY better out there.)

My apologies to the REAL person that taped this but I dunno who that is.

This still may be a new source.

I am VERY SORRY about this mistake.

I would NEVER claim I taped something that I didn't.

01/03/2015: Update:

It has been reported that this IS a NEW audience source: (the text seen is completely wrong due to the tapes error/mix up but it IS a new source)

"Your source does NOT match either of the two current AUDs in the DB (Friend's or Wagner's). What you have is a new source for us.

I believe all three sources were taped on the floor. Right after Jerry sings "drag your body down" some dude yells Waahoo really loud. You can hear him on all three AUD sources, but in each source it's from a different perspective. Otherwise, the crowd chatter is different on all three sources, but I think the tapers were set up near each other, generally in the area of the SBD as would have happened back in those days."

Once again, this isn't from what I taped but is a different pull all together. The taper is unknown at this time.
MY masters sound like crap & are not worth circulating.
I simply got them wrong, mixed up, and I went on to upload what I thought, (at the time), was my recording but had grabbed this aud copy instead. I didn't realize my error until after I had made the text file you see & uploaded it.

hope this explains the mistake I made.

thanks for all your efforts... ...& your honesty for posterity.

I love this show
